Key Match Events: Phoenix Suns guard Devin Booker and forward Ryan Dunn and Memphis Grizzlies guard Cam Spencer and forward-center Jaren Jackson Jr. react during the fourth quarter of the game at Footprint Center.
The Phoenix Suns are now two games under .500 after falling to the Memphis Grizzlies on New Year's Eve.
Post-Match Reflections: “The frustration level is high. We’re all competitors in here and we realize these games are going to cost us in the end of the season," said Devin Booker after the game.

"We have guys that have won at a high level, that have high expectations," Phoenix head coach Mike Budenholzer said. "We gotta find ways to get better, so these are not easy times. But our guys will find a way through it, and we’ll find a way through it together."
